body:
Hello,

I have a component this way :

```
var IconesSVG = React.createClass({
    getInitialState: function() {
        return {icones:{
            icone1: {positions: [[1,56],[-2,57],[-3, 58],[-8, 59]]}
        }}
    },
    componentDidMount:function() {
        var c = this
        setTimeout(function() {
            c.setState({icones:{
                icone1: {positions: [[2,58],[3,57],[4, 59],[-8, 59], [-11, 60], [-12, 61]]}
                }})
        }, 4000)
    },

    render: function() {
        var c = this
        var icones = _.keys(c.state.icones).map(function(uuid) {
            return c.state.icones[uuid].positions.map(function(position, index) {
                var pixels = c.props.projection(position)
                return <use key={index} x={pixels[0]} y={pixels[1]} xlinkHref={"#" + uuid} />
            })
        })
        return (
                <g>
                    {test}
                    {icones}
                </g>
            )
    }
})
```

When the component is mounted everything works as espected : the different locations of <use /> are rendered properly:

But when the state is updated (here after 4 sec for the demonstration), the new elements are not displayed. They are in fact present in the DOM, but not displayed probably due to issues with namespace. When I cut & paste them with firefox tools in the same place, they suddenly appear.
